casebody.data:
The State of Ohio, Appellee, v. Winningham, Appellant.

[Cite as State v. Winningham, 132 Ohio St.3d 77, 2012-Ohio-1998.]

(No. 2012-0099 Submitted March 20, 2012 Decided May 10, 2012.)

{¶ 1} The discretionary appeal is accepted.

{¶ 2} The judgment of the court of appeals is vacated, and the cause is remanded to the court of common pleas for application of United States v. Jones, — U.S.-, 132 S.Ct. 945, 181 L.Ed.2d 911 (2012).

O’Connor, C.J., and Pfeifer, Lundberg Stratton, O’Donnell, Lanzinger, Cupp, and McGee Brown, JJ., concur. *78Joseph T. Deters, Hamilton County Prosecuting Attorney, and Melynda Machol, Assistant Prosecuting Attorney, for appellee. Raymond L. Katz, for appellant.
